==English==

===Etymology===

From Chaucer's character '''[[w:Pandarus|Pandarus]]'''. (See also Shakespeare's [[wikibooks:Troilus and Cressida|Troilus and Cressida]])

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-pander.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''pander'''
# A person who furthers the [[illicit]] [[romance]] of others. (Later [[panderer]].)
# An offer of illicit [[sex]] with a third party.
# An illicit or illegal [[offer]], usually to [[tempt]].

===Verb===
'''pander'''
# To offer illicit sex with a third party, to [[pimp]].
# To tempt, usually by appealing to improper motivators such as religious bias or racist opinions.

